==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sorehon
<hw>Sore"hon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted from
<ets>sojourn</ets>, Scot. <ets>soirne</ets>, <ets>sorn</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Formerly, in Ireland, a kind of servile tenure which subjected the
tenant to maintain his chieftain gratuitously whenever he wished to
indulge in a revel.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorel</ent>⟦br⟧
